**Document Summary for DevOps Technician:**

**1. Primary Guidelines and Requirements:**
   - **Connected Government Act (H.R.2331):** All newly developed or redesigned federal agency public websites must be mobile-friendly from July 2018 onwards.
   - **Mobile-Friendly Requirement:** Websites should be navigable and accessible via mobile devices, such as smartphones and tablets.

**2. Security:**
   - **Navigating the Future of Mobile Services:** Provides guidance on vetting the security of mobile apps based on standards and agency best practices. [Source](https://www.atarc.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/ATARC-MSCT-Report-Navigating-Future-of-Mobile-Services.pdf)
   - **DHS Study on Mobile Device Security:** Highlights threats to federal government's use of mobile devices and recommends security improvements. [Source](https://www.digitalgov.gov/2017/05/04/dhs-study-on-mobile-device-security/)
   - **CIO Council Federal Secure Mobility Toolkit:** Offers a collection of secure mobility success stories and best practices for agencies. [Source](https://cioknowledge.max.gov/?q=system/files/attachment/Federal%20Secure%20Mobility%20Toolkit.pdf)

**3. Accessibility:**
   - **Accessibility for Teams:** Encourages understanding of diverse roles in practicing accessibility across design, development, and product management. [Source](https://digital.gov/2018/07/10/introducing-accessibility-for-teams/)
   - **Federalist Platform:** Provides hosting with built-in compliance to Section 508 Standards, supporting accessibility requirements. [Source](https://digital.gov/2017/06/05/federalist-is-out-of-beta-and-open-for-business/)
   
**4. User Experience (UX):**
   - **Mobile User Experience Guidelines:** Offers practical UX DOs and DON'Ts to assist federal agencies in developing efficient mobile interfaces. [Source](https://digital.gov/resources/mobile-user-experience-guidelines-and-recommendations/)
   - **Youâ€™ll Have Them at Swipe Webinar:** Discusses approaches to enhance mobile user experiences. [Source](https://www.digital.gov/2013/02/11/youll-have-them-at-swipe-making-an-awesome-mobile-user-experience-webinar/)

**5. Compliance:**
   - **Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG):** Federal websites need to comply with these guidelines to ensure content is accessible to all users, including those with disabilities.
   - **Digital Analytics Program (DAP):** Offers tools for measuring and enhancing compliance with federal digital standards.

**6. Performance and Development Tools:**
   - **Mobile Development and Testing with Chrome DevTools:** Outlines how this tool can be used for responsive, mobile-first web experiences. [Source](https://www.digitalgov.gov/2016/11/21/mobile-development-and-testing-with-chrome-devtools/)
   - **Responsive Design Techniques:** Tips for crafting flexible web page layouts that adapt to different devices. [Source](https://www.digitalgov.gov/2013/06/11/responsive-design/)

**Brief Summary:**
DevOps should prioritize implementing mobile-friendly design as per the Connected Government Act, ensuring robust security practices, maintaining strong accessibility compliance to meet Section 508 Standards, and enhancing user experience for mobile interfaces. Utilize available government-provided resources, tools like Chrome DevTools for testing, and keep up with WCAG guidelines for compliance.